parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to severe injuries or fatalities, as the vehicle's occupants may not receive the necessary protection to prevent harm.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy despite significant damage to the vehicle
resulting in injuries or fatalities to occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle wobbles on the road
the brakes feel unresponsive during quick stops
the brakes make a noise
the vehicle takes longer to stop than expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective rear door sealant can cause water to penetrate the rear seats, leading to water damage, mold, and mildew, which can compromise the vehicle's interior and potentially affect the health and safety of occupants.
symptoms: Water enters the rear seats when it rains
water damage
mold
and mildew in the rear seats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the single blade windshield wiper can reduce visibility during rain or snow, increasing the risk of accidents, and may also cause inconvenience and discomfort to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The windshield wiper blade hits below the windshield
the windshield wiper blade stops working
difficulty finding replacement sub-blades
only regular 26-inch blades are available for purchase.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the single blade windshield wiper may be inadequate, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially during inclement weather.
symptoms: The windshield wiper blade hits below the windshield
difficulty finding replacement sub-blades
only regular 26-inch blades are available for purchase.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Abnormal Vehicle Alignment and Anti-Lock Braking System (ABS) Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The misalignment of the vehicle can cause uneven tire wear, reduced traction, and compromised handling, increasing the risk of accidents. The faulty ABS system can lead to unexpected braking behavior, further exacerbating the safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle tilts or leans to one side
the vehicle wobbles or vibrates while driving
the ABS system engages unnecessarily
especially when driving over curbs
the vehicle jumps or jerks when driving in slow traffic
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The small and potentially mispositioned brake pedal can cause the driver's foot to slip off, leading to delayed or failed braking, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The driver's foot slips off the brake pedal
especially when slowing down or stopping
requiring extra caution and attention while driving.
